## What I Am Still Thinking About

One practical question that came up during the RDS encryption documentation: how should the SSP handle the fact that RDS encryption can only be enabled at instance creation?

If an organization is documenting SC-28 for an existing unencrypted RDS instance, the implementation description cannot honestly say "encryption is enabled" — it would need to say "encryption is not currently enabled; implementation requires creating a new encrypted RDS instance from an encrypted snapshot." That is a POA&M item, not an implemented control.

For MyClinic's OpenMRS deployment, the assumption throughout this project is that the RDS instance was created with encryption enabled from the beginning — which is the correct approach when standing up a new system. But for organizations doing remediation work on existing deployments, the SSP writing for SC-28 might surface that a re-architecture task is needed to implement the control. That is valuable to discover through documentation rather than through a breach.

