## What's Next

Day 51 continues the SSP documentation with administrative and operational controls — policies, training, contingency planning, and incident response procedures. The technical controls documented today are necessary but not sufficient. The administrative controls are what give the technical controls operational continuity — ensuring that the MFA requirement is enforced for new accounts, that the quarterly access review actually happens, and that when an incident occurs the response is consistent and documented.

